description: Emergency Response to Influenza Outbreak in Ukraine

subproject.description:
1.1.	Emergency Response Center (ERC) established to (1) enable a better coordination of emergency situations; (2) ensure needs assessment, emergency preparedness and response; (3) assist the Government of Ukraine in coordination of international community’s assistance
1.2.	A comprehensive response plan is developed to assist the Government of Ukraine in disaster prevention, preparedness and response.
2. Government has resources to ensure effective social communication in emergency situations/fighting influenza outbreaks
3. Government supported as necessary in effective logistical and technical services in emergency situations/fighting the influenza outbreak.
